author: Jessica Floum
title: Northeast Portland families face tough choice after property manager more than doubles their rent
text: The Ku-Castillos fear they will have to move out of their northeast Portland apartment building, where they celebrate Christmas each year with their extended Mexican family. It's where Eric Ku comes home each weeknight at 11 p.m. after working two kitchen jobs to pay the rent and where pencil marks on a bedroom door document Ku-Castillo and her three younger siblings growth over the past seven years.
